snippet.textDisplay:
This whole business has become a joke. Nobody even seems to know for sure if  Australian law even provides for the type of exemption he claims to have in the first place. The ex-minister interviewed by the BBC  yesterday said there was no such exemption. Even if there is an exemption, is it an exemption to enter without vaccination but with quarantine or a total exemption from everything?
Immigration Australia appear to have been unusually incompetent in refusing him entry without due process. The judge then lets him into Australia unvaccinated and unquarantined, on the basis of this error, without any examination of the actual facts of the refusal of entry. It would make sense for the judge to cancel the decision to refuse entry and refer it back for review and re-assessment ensuring that proper procedures and due process are followed rather than just allowing this unvaccinated and unquarantined individual to enter Australia and mix freely. If he is infectious, the damage is now done and it was done by this judge. 
The false declaration on some form or other means nothing. Which form was it anyway? People seem to think that it was his visa application form, but that makes no sense and cannot be as the visa was granted in November and any question about travel all that time ago would have no meaning in the context of his entry. The IPC does not ask this question and as this form is given out and completed in the aircraft could not have been completed by his agent. So what form was it please? A special Covid form I imagine but it would have to have been completed on or immediately prior to arrival in order for the have you travelled within the last 14 days to have any meaning. I accept that lieing on an official form could in theory be cause for refusal of entry, but as this was not discovered until after the initial refusal can have no bearing on the initial decision.
He has been given so much special treatment. Immediate court cases; even a hearing on Sunday. Never heard of such a thing in respect of a simple refusal of entry and when was the last time you heard of a court case on a Sunday? Now the Minister has acted and decided to remove him from Australia on these new grounds, but still without any consideration of the correctness in law of the original decision.
This whole business has become a media circus and a joke. He should just have been put on the next plane home like any other immigration refusal.
